description.plain:
Royce Cornell Davison (b. September 19, 1996), better known by the stage name Ugly God, is a rapper and producer from Houston, Texas, and Biloxi, Mississippi. He is fluent in Spanish, as his parents hailed from the Dominican Republic.

Ugly God originally rapped as Pussy Bacon but changed his stage name per his mother’s request. He released his first song, “I Beat My Meat,” in the summer of 2014, but two basketball coaches made him take it down on separate occasions. He finally re-released it in July 2015.

Ugly God briefly attended the University of Southern Mississippi before dropping out to pursue a rap career.

In March 2016, Ugly God released his viral hit, “Water,” which eventually made its way onto the Billboard Hot 100.

He released his debut mixtape, The Booty Tape, on August 4, 2017.

On April 23, 2018, Ugly God released his first EP, just a lil something before the album…, which served as a teaser for his debut studio album.

His debut album, Bumps & Bruises, was released on August 9, 2019.

description.plain:
On this viral hit, Ugly God raps about his sexual prowess, correlating his ability to attract women to “Water.” This is the lead single to The Booty Tape.

“Water” marks Ugly God’s only solo appearance on the Billboard Hot 100; it peaked at #80 during the week of February 3, 2017.

songs.full_title: I Beat My Meat by Ugly God
songs.title: I Beat My Meat

description.plain:
On the sexual song “I Beat My Meat,” Ugly God declares his affection for masturbating. Throughout the track, Royce describes his use for “beating his meat” rather than engaging in intercourse.

The song gained more notoriety after a Youtube video of four dancers taking turns dancing to the song while making sexual gestures incorporated in their moves.

In a November 2016 interview with DJ Vlad, Ugly God commented on “I Beat My Meat,” admitting he was a virgin during the creation of the song.

In the same interview, Royce also mentioned that the song was removed off Soundcloud three times, stating:


I was actually good at basketball, I was real good. And, uhm, they felt like I wanted to pursue a basketball career. And, that didn’t, you know, compliment it with the song.

So you put it back up, and they made you take it down again? [Ugly God nods.] Ok, how many views did it get this second time around? It got to like 13K, 12K. […] So then why did you put it back up? Like I said, I just like doing this—I just liked it.

So what happened the third time? Fuckin' internet got to it, I think. Internet got to it, fuckin', viral videos, people dancing to it. Shit like that.


The Apple iOS Ringtone “Opening (Default)” was used as the sample for the song.
